[MOTHERSHIP GIVEAWAY]
•
We're giving away a Cambridge Audio YOYO (L) Home Audio System worth $650! This bluetooth speaker is compatible with a number of inputs, such as Bluetooth, HDMI ARC, TOSLINK optical and aux connections.
•
All you have to do is:
1. Follow @mothershipsg & @warnermusicsg.
2. Listen to Dua Lipa’s new album “Future Nostalgia” on Spotify.
3. Tell us which is your favorite song off the album and why.
•
Giveaway ends this coming Sunday, May 10, 2020 at 7pm, and is only open to those residing in Singapore.
Do note that the prize will only be delivered after the end of the circuit breaker period. Good luck!
Hallucinate because the tune is so CATCHY 🎶🎶🎵
Definitely "Cool". Because the song is cool amirite ;). Ngl the song is straight up vibe + match my workout pacing. Overall the whole album is amazing lol
I love dont start now as the lyrics and beat is super catchy,it also keeps me hyped up
My favourite song is definitely the " Don't Start Now " as it's one of the best song I've ever heard in my entire life plus the lyrics are lit!!!❤️❤️🙌🙌

Break My Heart💔 this song is so relatable and so catchy!! It always reminds me of what I should do but then I am so soft hearted. Falling for someone that could break my heart, but then listening to sad songs are just too not enough. After blasting to Dua Lisa's Break My Heart, dance one round, i feel so much better. I feel much stronger, music is always a therapy for me!! I need music to survive!! Thanks for this awesome giveaway and may I have it so I can have an awesome audio system at home to blast BREAK MY HEART!!!
dont start now because i love how catchy it is & has a nice vibe💗🔥😍

My favourite has got to be the title track “Future Nostalgia”!! Love the lyrics and the concept of female empowerment!! “I know you ain’t used to a female alpha” is my favourite line. Totally relatable and now I know what to say to “them”.. ANDDD the blend of pop and electro makes the music so so catchy🤩 I want to dance and groove to all Dua Lipa’s songs while playing them on the Cambridge Audio YOLO (L) Home Audio System!!💃😌
Don't start now!! Cos it has that groovy catchy beat. Plus it's pretty trendy on tik tok!!
dont start now because it gets me feeling the vibe!
favorite song is “Don’t Start Now” cos i dont even wanna started to explain on how staying at home is making me so unproductive and bored 😭😭
My favourite song from the album is Hallucinate!! because it reminds me of me hallucinating from overdose of staying at home 🤓
“Good In Bed” becos cb is helping me get more sleep
My favourite song from the album is "Physical"! Because circuit breaker is allowing to have more to time workout at home! 💪🏻

My fav is def BREAK MY HEART💔 Cos it’s a super easy song to sing along with and the dance is shooo cute to follow along too❤️😍 PLUS! Her lyrics are just right for CB because she said that we should’ve stayed at home, APPLYING TO THOSE WHO BREAKING RULES🌚🌚🌚😂😂

My favourite song is boys will be boys because #girlsruntheworld 😍 and its a song that rly highlights a more serious issue at hand!! 😭 love dua’s voice in this song, and its perfect with the arrangement. Am such a lover of her songs! 🔥 Would really love the home system because ive been looking for studio monitors and headphones during this cb period to go serious and make my own music, and dua and jasmine from warner really inspire me to do that. Hope i get this! it’s really something that will help me alot. 🥳❤️ peace out

My favourite song is Don’t Start Now! 🙋🏼‍♂️ I love the song for its energy, the positive vibes and the feeling~! It is one song I always use to motivate myself, be it exercising or even when I am feeling blue~ ✌🏼 Awesome Song 👍
Dont start now cuz its juz catchy and super amazing
My favourite song is “don’t start now”. A must-listen for my workouts, love the beats, extremely motivating!
Mine will be “Physical” as the song is very catchy and light hearted.

My favorite song without a doubt is Dont Start Now because not only is it catchy but I just got out of a really toxic relationship and it really shows me how in the end he’s not worth it. I really did a full 180 and I’m all good already and so moved on it’s scary

🤣🤣 Good in Bed cause this WFH makes me stay a longer time in bed, that sometimes I don’t feel like moving off despite having to work. Or worse, I migrate to my bed to work and you can guess what happens next HAHA

My favourite song is Physical because my mum is an avid fan of ZUMBA and the song reminds me of her grit and determination to stay fit and healthy despite the fact that she is ageing❣️ At the same time, I would want to win this speaker as a gift to her because she has been doing livestream zumba using the speakers off her phone only and it is really not the most conducive or motivating to stay physical🥺 SHALL WE GIFT HER THIS TO MOTIVATE HER TO “GET PHYSICAL” and keep moving???
Rip you have to listen to dua lipa to win?

I really love all the songs!!! Some of them really open me up to new genres of modern day music (pop). As someone who tends to listen to slow-tempo songs in the genres of Jazz, lofi, R&B/Hip-hop, Classical music and Ballads, this album really opened me up to many different interpretations to pop music drum rhythms and styles to it. The album has also opened me up to many new songs to binge-listen to when im in the mood to grove a little to some music. I really enjoyed the album and all the different themes, the styles that she experimented with like some bits and pieces of like ‘80s or ‘90s vibes in the songs. Im really looking forward to more music from her!!
